Conclusion As in ancient times, the current society is based on a reckless preference for its own benefit, regardless of the social interest.
By its very nature, private capital is no longer able to understand and exercise social benefits.
The result is now, as then, the unprecedented decadence of the elites without any effort to reform the deeper nature.
So we must look for the causality of the onset of fascist and communist regimes in the reckless liberalization of the economic systems of the 19th and 20th centuries.
In the current situation, the demise of these systems in favour of a liberal-type democracy can be considered a certain break with the expectation of another round.
