Under pressure of competition, both at international and internal European level, the government of the Czech Republic will continue to seek ways to further reduce the social level of the population.
This trend is therefore systemic.
The solution is targeted political-social reforms, which will strengthen the state's participation in the economy, strengthen citizens' influence on the government and weaken the monopoly position of private capital in society in favour of the state.
