Last time the birth rate exceeded 2, which is considered a recovery rate, in 1976.
Why don't the Singaporens have more children?
Tan Wei Ming, director of the Department of Marriage and Family of the National Bureau of Population, says it's because of "better education" and "a wider range of career opportunities".
