Santos and Ortega will meet on Saturday in Mexico, where they are to participate in the inauguration of President Enrique Peñi Nieta.
In the framework of the summit, the EU Defence Ministers met in advance to approve the 2013 Action Plan, which seeks to strengthen dialogue and consensus on the area's defence.
The members of UNASUR are Argentina, Bolivia, Colombia, Ecuador, Peru, Brazil, Uruguay, Venezuela, Chile, Guyana, Suriname and Paraguay, although the last country in question is currently excluded.
Peru is the provisional chairman of this regional block.
